# System Architecture Diagram

This diagram illustrates the flow of a user query through the KPN Intelligent Agent, highlighting the separation between the AI services and the functional tools.

```mermaid
graph TD
    %% Styling
    classDef client fill:#f9f,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef api fill:#bbf,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef ai fill:#dfd,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef tool fill:#ffd,stroke:#333,stroke-width:2px;
    classDef data fill:#eee,stroke:#333,stroke-dasharray: 5 5;

    %% Components
    User((User/Client)):::client
    API[FastAPI Endpoint]:::api
    
    subgraph AI_Core ["AI Orchestration Layer"]
        Orchestrator[Agentic Orchestrator - GPT-4]:::ai
        Embeddings[Azure OpenAI Embeddings]:::ai
    end

    subgraph Tool_Layer ["Intelligent Toolset"]
        RAG[kpn_annual_report_search]:::tool
        Products[kpn_products_tool]:::tool
        News[kpn_news_tool]:::tool
    end

    subgraph Knowledge_Data ["Data Sources"]
        FAISS[(FAISS Vector DB)]:::data
        Docs[Local Documents - PDF/DOCX]:::data
        Static[Internal Product Knowledge]:::data
        Web[KPN News Website]:::data
    end

    %% Connections
    User -->|Query| API
    API -->|Input| Orchestrator
    
    Orchestrator -->|Calls| RAG
    Orchestrator -->|Calls| Products
    Orchestrator -->|Calls| News
    
    RAG -->|Similarity Search| Embeddings
    Embeddings -->|Vector| FAISS
    FAISS -.->|Context| RAG
    Docs -->|Ingestion| FAISS
    
    Products -->|Retrieve| Static
    News -->|Scrape| Web
    
    RAG -.->|Retrieved Data| Orchestrator
    Products -.->|Product Info| Orchestrator
    News -.->|Latest Headlines| Orchestrator
    
    Orchestrator -->|Final Answer| API
    API -->|Synthesis| User

    %% Subgraph Styling
    style AI_Core fill:#f0fff0,stroke:#2e8b57
    style Tool_Layer fill:#fffaf0,stroke:#daa520
    style Knowledge_Data fill:#f8f8f8,stroke:#808080
```

### Flow Highlights for Demo:
1. **User Interaction**: Query enters via a professional REST API.
2. **AI Service Separation**: The "Brain" (GPT-4) resides in the AI Core, separate from the execution logic of the tools.
3. **Embeddings**: Used specifically for the RAG pipeline to ensure semantic accuracy when searching local KPN documents.
4. **Tool Decoupling**: Tools are independent Python modules that can be updated or expanded without touching the core AI logic.
